The adequacy of the allowance for losses is assessed quarterly. Three primary factors influencing the level of our
allowance for losses on customer financing receivables are customer credit ratings, default rates and collateral values.
We assign internal credit ratings for all customers and determine the creditworthiness of each customer based upon
publicly available information and information obtained directly from our customers. Our rating categories are
comparable to those used by the major credit rating agencies.
